overview: The user initiated a request to enhance the aesthetic appeal of their
  sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was functional but lacked
  visual sophistication. I began by conducting a detailed review of the existing
  styling across key files and components. Based on this analysis, I identified
  several areas for improvement, including the generic color palette, plain
  backgrounds, dense form sections, and basic UI elements. The implementation
  involved a complete redesign of the app's visual language. I introduced a
  calming, sleep-themed color palette, updated the main questionnaire form with
  decorative background elements and a refined progress indicator, and
  overhauled the welcome (IntroSection) and report sections with new layouts and
  improved visual hierarchy. Additionally, I polished individual UI components
  such as checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders to align with the new
  aesthetic. The goal was to transform the app from a generic template look to a
  more professional, trustworthy, and visually engaging experience tailored for
  a sleep health application. The changes were successfully compiled, and the
  next step was to verify them in the browser, though some minor technical
  issues with the browser tools were encountered at the end of the conversation.
